## Scoring Criteria

| Score | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| 9-10  | Excellent - Ship it |
| 7-8   | Good - Minor issues only |
| 5-6   | Acceptable - Some concerns |
| 3-4   | Poor - Significant issues |
| 1-2   | Unacceptable - Major rework needed |

## Approval Thresholds

- **Phase 2 (Validation)**: Score >= 6.0, no blocking issues
- **Phase 4 (Verification)**: Score >= 7.0, no critical/high issues

## Review Checklist

### Architecture Review
- [ ] Clear separation of concerns
- [ ] Appropriate use of design patterns
- [ ] Sensible module/package structure
- [ ] Dependencies are justified
- [ ] Error boundaries are well-defined

### Code Quality Review
- [ ] Functions have single responsibility
- [ ] Code is readable and self-documenting
- [ ] Naming conventions are consistent
- [ ] No unnecessary complexity
- [ ] Comments explain WHY, not WHAT

### Performance Review
- [ ] No obvious N+1 query patterns
- [ ] Appropriate use of caching (if applicable)
- [ ] No blocking operations in hot paths
- [ ] Resource cleanup is handled

### Testing Review
- [ ] Tests cover happy path
- [ ] Edge cases are tested
- [ ] Error conditions are tested
- [ ] Tests are maintainable

